note_header uses echo | grep | head | sed. When grep finds no match,
it exits 1, which kills the pipeline under set -euo pipefail. This is
the same bug class as the 'grep -qF breaks on --- prefixes' warning
on test.sh. Fixed with || true at the end of the pipeline.

This pattern exists in many places throughout the tool — any function
that uses grep in a pipeline is vulnerable. The || true fix is local;
a more systematic fix would use awk instead of grep for header extraction.
